### Service Registry
# Open http://localhost:8761 in the browser to view the Eureka dashboard.

### User Service API Requests (Port 8081)

# Create User
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com"
}

###

# Get User by ID
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1

###

# Get All Users
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users

###

### Product Service API Requests (Port 8082)

# Create Product
POST http://localhost:8082/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Smartphone",
  "price": 699.99
}

###

# Get Product by ID
GET http://localhost:8082/api/products/1

###

# Get All Products
GET http://localhost:8082/api/products

###

### Order Service API Requests (Port 8083)

# Create Order
# Ensure User with ID 1 and Product with ID 1 exist in their respective services first.
POST http://localhost:8083/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

###

# Get Order by ID
GET http://localhost:8083/api/orders/1

###

# Get All Orders
GET http://localhost:8083/api/orders
